  "buggy_files": ["drivers/ata/libata-core.c"],
  "buggy_functions": ["ata_device_blacklist"],
  "confidence": 0.95,
  "reasoning": "The Samsung 860 EVO SSD is not included in the device quirks list (ata_device_blacklist array), so it is not being marked with the ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM flag. This causes the kernel to attempt queued TRIM operations with the device, which Samsung 860 EVO cannot properly handle, resulting in timeouts and lockups during fstrim. Similar Samsung models (SSD 840 and 850) are already in the quirks list with ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM flag at lines 4562-4565, but the 860 model is missing. The fix would be to add an entry for 'Samsung SSD 860*' with both ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM and ATA_HORKAGE_ZERO_AFTER_TRIM flags to disable queued TRIM support for this device."
}

